AB  - The following misprints occurred in “A Theorem on the Core of an Economy” by K. Vind in our January 1965 Issue.Page 47, line 18 should be … a new relation  if …Page 47, line 27 should be (2)  for all i in S.Page 47, line 31 should be … H ∩ UΓf = Φ, …Page 47, line 31 should be … Γi = .Page 48, line 3 should be … H ∩ Γi(ε) ≠ Φ….“The Relationship between Output and Employment in British Manufacturing Industries”, by F. Brechling.In the article of the above title which appeared in our July issue, the figures in the fourth and seventh columns of Table II were incorrect since the decimal place had been moved one place to the left. As a result all the numbers quoted are too small by a factor of ten.
